- testExcessReservationWillBeUnreserved - some comments do not match code, could you fix that too.

bq. In CS (before this patch), excessReservation won't be completed since ParentQueue.assignContainers doesn't copy the excessReservation field, so CapacityScheduler will not release such excessReservations.

[~leftnoteasy], quick question for my own education, before this patch, it seems that the attempt to fulfill a reservation always starts in the LeafQueue, i.e.
{code:title=CapacityScheduler#allocateContainersToNode|borderStyle=solid}
      LeafQueue queue = ((LeafQueue)reservedApplication.getQueue());
      CSAssignment assignment =
          queue.assignContainers(
              clusterResource,
              node,
              // TODO, now we only consider limits for parent for non-labeled
              // resources, should consider labeled resources as well.
              new ResourceLimits(labelManager.getResourceByLabel(
                  RMNodeLabelsManager.NO_LABEL, clusterResource)));
{code}

So there is no need for  ParentQueue.assignContainers to copy excessReservation field, right?

